s this.<br>
<br>
Let another Guild clear to a mob, then follow them and make them roll for a spawn? I don't think so!<br>
<br>
Zones like Fear inwhich a guild MUST CLEAR to get to a mob, then it's theirs until they FAIL at the mob. <br>
<br>
If a guild wants the AoW, they get it by killing Vindi, Statue, Idol. If you <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  EXPECT</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> a guild to then ROLL on who gets the AoW, your out of your mind. Theres a difference between the Ragefire camp and the Plane of Fear. The ragefire camp is camped usually by a lone cleric without the necessary force to kill ragefire. In those instances when ragefire does pop, the group who gets there with sufficient force gets the mob. If two or more guilds get there with sufficient force at about the same time, then a GM can force a roll.  <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  HOWEVER</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> the Wraith in PoF is different. Radiant apparently had &quot;SUFFICIENT FORCE&quot; present before ADD zoned in, cleared to the mob. Whether or not they aggroed the Wraith at this point is pointless. They were there first, they did the clearing, and by <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  ALL RIGHTS</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> have first shot at the Wraith. What ADD did in my eyes is <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  WRONG</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->.<br>
